<F P=100> ITALY &amp; VATICAN CITY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Denies Pope To Visit Iraq </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM0803144194 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 8 Mar 94 p 7 </F>
<F P=103> PM0803144194 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by 'Irfan Rashid: "Vatican Spokesman Tells </F>
AL-HAYAH: Pope Does Not Plan To Visit Iraq in the Near Future"] 
  [Excerpt] Rome -- A spokesman for the Vatican has denied 
reports that Pope John Paul II has accepted an invitation to 
visit Iraq "in the near future." He said: "The pope's program 
does not include anything that indicates the possibility of his 
visiting that country." 
  The spokesman did not confirm whether the pope had received 
an invitation. He told AL-HAYAH: "At any rate, sending an 
invitation officially or unofficially does not necessarily mean 
its acceptance and inclusion in the program of the pope's 
religious visits." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

