<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   EP Calls on UN, EU To Stop Serb Attacks in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1003210194 Paris AFP in English 2025 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1003210194 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Strasbourg, March 10 (AFP) -- The European 
Parliament Thursday [10 March] called on EU [European Union] 
member states to send more troops to war-torn Bosnia-Herzegovina 
to monitor a ceasefire in Sarajevo and have it extended to other 
regions 
  "NATO's riposte to Serb air forces which violated the 
Bosnian 
airspace has obviously had a salutary effect," a resolution 
adopted by European Union legislators said, referring to the 
downing by NATO fighters of four Serb warplanes over Bosnia last 
month. 
  The Parliament resolution said however that "the military 
aggression is being pursued and that Croats as well as Serbs 
continue to perpetrate atrocities in Bosnia-Hercegovina." 
  Parliament called on European Union ministers and the United 
Nations to take the necessary steps to immediately stop Serb 
militias from attacking Moslem-populated Srebrenica, Zepa, 
Maglaj, Tuzla and Bihac. 
  It also warned the Croatian government of sanctions if 
Zagreb 
continued to maintain troops in Bosnia-Herzegovina. 

</TEXT>

