<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moldova To Sign NATO's `Partnership for Peace' Accord </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1103105494 Paris AFP in English 1012 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1103105494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brussels, March 11 (AFP) -- Moldovan President 
Mircea Snegur will sign an agreement at NATO headquarters here 
Wednesday making his country the 12th to join the partnership 
for peace program, the North Atlantic Treaty Organization said 
Friday [11 March]. 
  The scheme, an alternative to full NATO membership offered 
to 
former East Bloc states, provides for joint maneuvers, planning, 
and peace maintenance operations. 
  Other countries that have joined the program are: Romania, 
Lithuania, Poland, Estonia, Hungary, Ukraine, Slovakia, 
Bulgaria, Latvia, Albania, and the Czech Republic. 

</TEXT>

