Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "Euro-Arab Delegates Acknowledge </F>
Importance of Continuing Peace Process"; as released by Brussels 
TEXTLINE database] 
  [Text] The third Euro-Arab meeting, held on Tuesday [8 
March], brought together 29 delegates from 14 Arab countries and 
several Members of the European Parliament [EP], who discussed 
political and economic support for the Middle East peace 
process, stability and security in the Arab world and Europe, 
and Euro-Arab economic cooperation. Recent events, especially 
the Hebron massacre, were in the forefront at this time, as 
participants observed a minute of silence in tribute to the 
victims at the opening of the session. All the delegations 
acknowledged the importance of continuing the peace process, 
noted Mr. Claude Cheysson (Socialist, French) at the press 
conference following the conclusion of the meeting. 
  Participants also insisted on the importance of providing 
protection for the Palestinian population under United Nations 
auspices. 

