<H3> <TI>   Dehaene, Czech Counterpart Meet 10 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1003132694 Prague CTK in English 1209 GMT 10 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1003132694 </F>
<F P=104>  Prague CTK </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brussels March 10 (CTK) -- Czech Prime Minister 
Vaclav Klaus met on Thursday [10 March] morning with his Belgian 
counterpart, Jean-Luc Dehaene, as part of his one-day working 
visit to European Union and NATO Headquarters. 
  The two pime ministers talked primarily about the European 
integration process, the development and vision of a more united 
Europe, and about future Czech membership in the European Union. 
  Dehaene told journalists afterwards that the meeting had 
been 
productive, and said he shared Klaus' "vision" of Europe. Klaus 
said the two of them agreed that a country like the Czech 
Republic must increase its ties to NATO, the EU and other 
international organisations. "We have to find something between 
association and full membership in the European Union," he said, 
adding that Dehaene had accepted his invitation to visit the 
Czech Republic in the near future. 
  Afterward Klaus met with European Commission President 
Jacques Delors. Commissioner for Foreign Relations Hans van den 
Broek was unable to attend the meeting as had been expected, 
since he was out of town in connection with talks on Norway's 
admission to the EU. 

</TEXT>

