<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Berlin, Estonia Sign Crime, Terrorism Agreement </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1003193894 Talinn Radio Talinn Network in Estonian 1200 
GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1003193894 </F>
<F P=104>  Talinn Radio Talinn Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Estonian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Estonian Interior Minister Heiki Arike and [Eduard] 
Lintner, the parliamentary state secretary at the German 
Ministry of Interior, have signed an intergovernmental agreement 
in Bonn, on cooperation in fighting organized crime, terrorism, 
and other serious crimes. According to the Estonian Interior 
Ministry's press service, Estonia will now have access to German 
databases and German experts for consultation and help in 
fighting such crimes as money laundering, drug business, 
forgeries of bank checks and credit cards, and terrorism, not 
customary in Estonia. The German Ministry of Interior has also 
promised to provide help to Estonia with staff training and 
equipment, as reported by the Interior Ministry's press service. 

</TEXT>

