<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   European Bank Loan Finances Saxony Gas Network </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1103121894 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1129 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1103121894 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Luxembourg/Dresden (ADN-lsc) [DDP/ADN's Saxony 
regional service] -- The European Investment Bank (EIB) in 
Luxembourg has made 80 million German marks available for the 
modernization and development of the gas supply network in 
eastern Saxony. The loan is to go to the Gasversorgung 
Sachsen-Ost GmbH (Gaso) [gas supply company] and is to help 
finance conversion from town gas to natural gas in the Dresden 
area, it was announced in Luxembourg 11 March by the EIB, which 
is responsible for long-term EU financial projects. 
  Work is to include laying over 100 km of pipes. Of these, 
half will involve the replacement of old pipes. The other half 
will be for laying pipes connecting new domestic and industrial 
consumers. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

