<H3> <TI>   Reports of Kola Nuclear Power Station Leak Dismissed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1003153494 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1400 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1003153494 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Finnish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Finnish Center for Radiation and Nuclear Safety 
is dismissing the reports of a leak at a nuclear power station 
in Kola yesterday as incorrect. The Center for Radiation and 
Nuclear Safety says that it has been in telephone contact with 
the nuclear power station in Kola. The station's chief engineer 
said nothing exceptional had taken place in the station this 
week. The German news agency DPA and AFP of France, quoting 
ITAR-TASS, reported that the third reactor at the Kola nuclear 
power station had had to be closed down. The reason given was 
unusual steam in the station building. 

