<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lamb Meets Kliridhis, Comments on Negotiations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1003123594 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1130 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1003123594 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Robert Lamb, U.S. State Department special 
coordinator on Cyprus, repeated that both sides are negotiating 
seriously and constructively on the proposals for the 
confidence-building measures. However, he expressed the view 
that one cannot speak of significant progress in the 
negotiations. Speaking after a meeting with President Glavkos 
Kliridhis this morning, Lamb noted that even the people who 
oppose aspects of the confidence-building measures should 
realize that the proposals for the measures are a reality and 
that these proposals are on the negotiating table. Responding 
to a question, though, on the end-of-March deadline for 
conclusion of an agreement on the confidence-building measures, 
Lamb was unclear about maintaining it. He said that the 
procedure must advance quickly but with care. Time, he noted, 
is an important aspect but all should feel comfortable in the 
negotiations and there should be no feeling that the process 
moves hastily. The target, Lamb said, is not so much the 
deadline but for progress in the procedure as quickly as 
possible. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

