<H3> <TI>   Kliridhis Denies Link Between Varosha, Passports </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1003124894 Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network in Greek 1130 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1003124894 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia Cyprus Broadcasting Corporation Radio 
Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Glavkos Kliridhis said in the most 
explicit manner that during the talks on the confidence-building 
measures [CBM's], the UN secretary general's representatives 
never directly or indirectly, orally or in writing, suggested 
that the Greek Cypriot side would get Famagusta's fenced-off 
area [Varosha] in exchange for recognizing the so-called Turkish 
Cypriot passports. 
  In a written statement on press reports on safe access to 
and 
from Famagusta, Kliridhis added that they have no connection to 
the UN suggestions. The president said that these press reports 
give the United Nations the impression that we are trying to 
create an excuse to reject the CBM's. 

