<F P=100> CYPRUS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Denktas on UN Report Calling Kliridhis `President' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1003154194 Ankara ANATOLIA in English 1520 GMT 10 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1003154194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara ANATOLIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Lefkosa, Mar. 10 (A.A.) -- Turkish Republic of 
Northern Cyprus (TRNC) President Rauf Denktas criticized on 
Thursday [10 March] a report of U.N. Secretary General Butrus 
Butrus-Ghali, on the indirect talks being held in Cyprus 
concerning the confidence-building measures. 
  In a statement from the TRNC capital, Denktas also announced 
that he had postponed a meeting scheduled for this afternoon 
with U.N. envoy Gustave Feissel, to Friday. 
  He said that he was to review the draft document given to 
him 
by the envoy, together with the prime minister and consultants. 
  "An incomphrehensible haste prevails in U.N. circles," he 
said. "This is not an issue that could be resolved in such a 
haste. Even a single word needs emphasis." 
  Denktas pointed out that the Butrus-Ghali report attributed 
a 
title to one of the sides, which is unacceptable to the other 
and that they would not accept Kliridhis being called 
"president," while he himself is referred to as "leader." 
  "The course of events are directed to support the `Cyprus 
republic' and to just mend us to it. [sentence as received] 
Therefore we shall continue to review the document put before 
us, very minutely," he said. 

</TEXT>

