<H3> <TI>   Temporary Lifting of FYROM Sanctions Rejected </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0903133694 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1230 GMT 9 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0903133694 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Responding to questions on the Skopje [The Former 
Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia--FYROM] issue, government 
spokesman Evangelos Venizelos today said that American and 
European efforts on the Skopje issue tend to be in the same 
direction on the matter of how they should formulate the 
preliminary conditions for dialogue between the two sides. He 
stressed that the coordinator of the efforts is Cyrus Vance. 
  The government spokesman also said that there is no 
possibility for a temporary lifting of the measures against 
Skopje and that Greece will lift the measures only when Skopje 
gives practical signs of goodwill, as demanded by the Greek 
side. A temporary suspension of the measures to allow a 
resumption of the dialogue is not in the government's plans, 
Venizelos said. 

</TEXT>

