<H3> <TI>   NATO Official on Albania's Role in Balkans </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BR1103161294 Rome ANSAMAIL Database in English 144 GMT 11 
Mar 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR1103161294 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome ANSAMAIL Database </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article: "NATO/Bosnia: Albania's Role </F>
Highlighted by Bouvard"] 
  [Text] Tirana, 11 Mar (ANSA) -- Louis Bouvard, chairman of 
the North Atlantic Assembly -- the forum of NATO and ex-Warsaw 
Pact nations -- today told Albanian Defence Minister Safet 
Zhulali that Albania is a "true partner" of NATO and that there 
will be no lasting peace in the Balkans without the 
participation of Albania. 
  Bouvard stressed that Albania's associate membership in the 
North Atlantic Assembly was an important step in its integration 
with NATO. Zhulali described Bouvard's speech to the Albanian 
parliament as "the warmest ever" by a foreign political figure. 
  Zhulali asked for greater support to counteract the effects 
of the embargo on former Yugoslavia, and expressed the view that 
there will be no "definitive end" to the Balkan crisis without a 
solution to the Kosovo, the largely ethnic-Albanian enclave 
within Serbia. 

</TEXT>

