<H3> <TI>   Ruehe Broaches Baltic Situation With Lithuania's Gylys </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1103072894 Hamburg DPA in German 1659 GMT 10 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1103072894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- On Thursday [10 March], Defense 
Minister Volker Ruehe, of the Christian Democratic Union [CDU], 
met Lithuanian Foreign Minister Povilas Gylys for an exchange of 
opinions. The Defense Ministry has stated that the two 
ministers discussed the situation in the Baltic republics and 
the CIS. In addition, they also broached issues of European 
security architecture and bilateral cooperation. They also 
talked at great length about details of NATO's Partnership for 
Peace offer to the countries of East Europe. 
  Gylys had met Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel, of the Free 
Democratic Party of Germany [FDP], on Wednesday. That meeting 
was also attended by Estonian Minister Without Portfolio Juri 
Luik and Latvian Foreign Minister Georgs Andrejevs. After his 
talks, Kinkel warned Moscow against "adding" further conditions 
to delay the 31 August 1994 deadline for the withdrawal of the 
Russian forces from Estonia and Latvia. 

</TEXT>

