<H3> <TI>   Rexrodt Expects 450,000 More Unemployed in 1994 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1203213894 Hamburg DPA in German 1206 GMT 12 Mar 04--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1203213894 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Munich (DPA) -- In 1994, on an annual average, 
FRG Economics Minister Guenter Rexrodt (Free Democratic Party of 
Germany) expects approximately 450,000 more unemployed than last 
year, despite an economic growth of 1 to 1.5 percent. The 
reduction of jobs in large enterprises is continuing and cannot 
be balanced by new jobs in small and medium-sized enterprises, 
Rexrodt said at the opening of the 46th International Trade Fair 
(IHM) in Munich (until 20 March) on Saturday [12 March]. 
  The end of the employment crisis can be expected in 1995 at 
the earliest, with a presumable growth of 2 to 2.5 percent. 
Rexrodt, Trade President Heribert Spaeth, and Bavarian Minister 
President Edmund Stoiber (Christian Social Union) paid tribute 
to the latest wage agreements and the first step toward more 
flexible working hours as a step in the right direction. Labor 
costs are too high, it was stated. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

