<F P=100> GERMANY </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kinkel on FDP Defeat </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403112894 Berlin DDP/ADN in German 1035 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1403112894 </F>
<F P=104>  Berlin DDP/ADN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DDP/ADN) -- This morning the Free Democratic 
Party [FDP] Presidium described its election defeat in Lower 
Saxony as a warning not to be ignored. Before the FDP Executive 
meeting which followed, party chairman Klaus Kinkel said it is 
now time to "roll up our sleeves." 
  Kinkel regards the FDP's difficulty as walking a tightrope 
between loyalty to the coalition and taking a position of its 
own: "The FDP has the problem that it is a coalition partner in 
Bonn and, as far as actual issues and style are concerned, it 
wants to bring this coalition to a respectable end and it will 
do so. On the other hand, we have to show independence. So we 
are caught in a bind." 

</TEXT>

