<H3> <TI>   Albanians Protest, Demand Kosovo Recognition </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1303202694 Tirana TVSH Television Network in Albanian 1900 
GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> AU1303202694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tirana TVSH Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Albanian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tens of thousands of Albanians gathered in Bonn's 
main square today for a protest rally under the motto "To 
recognize the Republic of Kosova as a sovereign and neutral 
state." German Deputy Peter Reuschenbach greeted the rally. 
Here is a report by Mimoza Cika: 
  [Cika] With their participation today in the protest under 
the leadership of the Kosova Democratic Alliance [LDK] branch, 
all Albanians who live and work in Germany showed that they are 
living proof of the national and political determination and 
devotion. 
  LKD Branch Chairman Afiz Gagica addressed the demonstrators 
and stressed the motto of this protest. 
  Mr. Peter Reuschenbach, chairman of the parliamentary group 
to the German Bundestag for Albania, also greeted the 
demonstrators. 
  Various representatives of high-level German organizations 
and bodies also greeted the rally participants. The petitions 
addressed to the high-level German authorities are based on the 
main demands to stop the violence and the Serbian systematic 
state terror against the Albanian population in Kosova and to 
prevent the eruption of an armed conflict in the Republic of 
Kosova by withdrawing the armed police forces from the Republic 
of Kosova. They also asked Germany and the united international 
states to recognize the independence of the Republic of Kosova. 

</TEXT>

