<H3> <TI>   Bundestag Adopts Law on Bonn-to-Berlin Move </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1103135394 Munich SUEDDEUTSCHE ZEITUNG in German 11 Mar 94 
p 1 </F>

<F P=103> AU1103135394 </F>
<F P=104>  Munich SUEDDEUTSCHE ZEITUNG </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by "dr": "Move Must Not Cost More Than 20 Billion"] </F>
  [Excerpt] Bonn -- The Berlin-Bonn Law, which settles the 
move of the Bundestag and the Federal Government to Berlin, was 
adopted with a large majority on Thursday [10 March]. According 
to this law, the operation is to be concluded by the year 2000. 
Speakers of the Bundestag groups of the Christian Democratic 
Union, Christian Social Union, and Free Democratic Party of 
Germany stressed that the cost ceiling set by the FRG finance 
minister at 20 billion marks must be observed. This also 
includes financial compensation measures for the affected cities 
of Bonn and Berlin. The decision envisages that the "central 
part" of the government functions will be moved to Berlin but 
that certain "political fields" will remain in Bonn. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

