<F P=100> SPAIN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government To Send 200 Extra Troops to Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1203110894 Madrid RNE International in Spanish 0900 GMT 12 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1203110894 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid RNE International </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In response to the request from the United Nations 
to increase the number of soldiers in the conflict zone, Spain 
will send to Bosnia-Herzegovina about 200 more blue helmets, who 
will join the Spanish UN battalion next week. In all, the new 
Spanish contribution will comprise around 200 men, who will be 
joining the 1,200 Spanish blue helmets stationed in the Mostar 
area. It is expected that they will be able to travel to the 
former Yugoslavia during the course of next week. According to 
an official spokesman, a radar detection unit, which locates 
mortar and heavy weapon trajectories, will be sent. The unit 
will comprise six vehicles and 25 men, who will have the task of 
monitoring and consolidating the cease-fire in the city of 
Mostar, which is considered vital for the security of the 
population. 

</TEXT>

