<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Prime Minister Chernomyrdin Begins Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Signs Debt Repayment Agreement </H4>
<F P=102> LD1103181094 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1700 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1103181094 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Finnish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In Helsinki, Russian Prime Minister Viktor 
Chernomyrdin has assured that Russia will fully repay its debts 
to Finland, so that this question, which has been a stumbling 
block in the relations between the two countries, will be 
resolved. Prime Minister Chernomyrdin today started a two-day 
official visit to Finland. The first day's talks have 
concentrated on the bilateral questions and especially on 
questions of economy and trade. 
  An agreement was signed today with which Russia will pay 450 
million Finnish markkas [FMk] of its debt with arms deliveries. 
Finland's receivables from Russia are altogether nearly FMk8 
billion. Prime Minister Esko Aho was of the opinion that the 
payment of the debt to the Bank of Finland with arms deliveries 
was an excellent arrangement that suits Finland well. 

</TEXT>

