<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Prime Minister Chernomyrdin Begins Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Meets With Indistrial Leaders </H4>
<F P=102> LD1103181494 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1400 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1103181494 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Finnish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Industry in Finland hopes for a speedy solution to 
the financing problems in trade between Finland and Russia. 
Mining Counselor [honorary title] Krister Ahlstroem, the 
chairman of the Confederation of Finnish Industry and Employers, 
told Russian Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin, who visited the 
Confederation, that the industry is especially hoping for 
counterguarantees to be arranged. Ahlstroem also raised the 
Finnish companies' 6 billion Finnish markkas of receivables from 
Russia. According to Erik Forsman, the press director of the 
Confederation, the Russian prime minister did not promise a 
quick solution to the debt problems. 
  [Begin Forsman recording] Chernomyrdin's general assessment 
was that the debt looks a lot bigger from the Finnish side than 
from the point of view of Russia, when they are looking at 
Finland -- your 6 billion is not such a big matter -- but when 
you look at it from our point of view, it is a big matter. [end 
recording] 
  Chernomyrdin, who this morning arrived as a guest of Prime 
Minister Esko Aho, has in addition to meetings with 
industrialists had lunch with President Ahtisaari. The official 
talks of the prime ministers are now coming to an end at the 
State Banqueting Hall. 

</TEXT>

