<F P=103> NC1103160394 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens ELEVTHEROTIPIA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Following instructions by the Ministry of Finance, 
78 railway cars loaded with oil crossed yesterday at noon 
through the Idhomeni border station into Skopje [The Former 
Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia--FYROM]. The cars arrived at the 
Thessaloniki port one day before the embargo measures were 
adopted but were blocked because they were there when the 
embargo was adopted. However, customs officials were wondering 
why permission was given yesterday. 

