<H3> <TI>   Spokesman: Delivery Not `Political Gesture' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1103163894 Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network in 
Greek 1600 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1103163894 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens Elliniki Radhiofonia Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Commenting on the entry of about 70 railway wagons 
with oil into Skopje [The Former Yugoslav Republic of 
Macedonia--FYROM], government spokesman Evangelos Venizelos said 
that this was not a political gesture. He noted: This action 
is not linked politically with the Papoulias-Vance meeting; the 
wagons were in Greek territory before 16 February. 
  Responding to a question, Mr. Venizelos said that this was 
not a relaxation of the Greek measures and noted it is a matter 
of 4,500 tons of oil, which is only sufficient for the Skopje 
refinery's operation for half a day. 

</TEXT>

