<H3> <TI>   EU's Delors Delays Injunction on Embargo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1203152894 Athens ATHENS NEWS in English 12 Mar 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC1203152894 </F>
<F P=104>  Athens ATHENS NEWS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] Greece yesterday hailed the 10 March meeting 
between UN mediator Cyrus Vance and Foreign Minister Karolos 
Papoulias in Geneva as a positive step toward restarting the 
dialogue between Athens and Skopje [The Former Yugoslav Republic 
of Macedonia--FYROM]. [passage omitted] 
  Encouraging signs that the Skopje dispute was slowly heading 
toward a settlement also came from Paris, where EU Commission 
President Jacques Delors offered his own "gesture of goodwill." 
Describing Mr. Vance's mediation talks in Geneva as "very 
good," Mr. Delors said: "I intend to wait for a while, and 
delay initiating injunction proceedings against Greece for its 
economic measures. Athens should take this as a gesture of 
goodwill and understanding on my part." Mr. Delors acknowledged 
"the political side of the problem since Greece invokes reasons 
of internal security." 

</TEXT>

