<H3> <TI>   Cetin Terms EP Resolution `Unacceptable' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1103192894 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1700 
GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1103192894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] Foreign Minister Hikmet Cetin has stated that the 
resolution adopted by the European Parliament [EP] regarding the 
lifting of certain deputies' immunities is unacceptable adding 
that the reason for it is lack of information. 
  Answering reporters' questions in Eskisehir, Cetin pointed 
out that there is a wish to politicize the issue and take it 
outside its limits. Indicating that similar decisions have been 
taken in numerous countries, Cetin gave the lifting of four 
German deputies' immunities for holding an illegal demonstration 
as an example. 
  In answer to a question, Cetin stated that Turkey does not 
make concessions, the government being a government which cannot 
be coerced. 

