<H3> <TI>   Gas Deliveries Resume; Minister Headed for Kiev </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1103162894 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1100 
GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1103162894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over video] </F>
  [Text] 205,000 cubic meters of natural gas arrived in 
Turkey today, one day after the natural gas delivery was 
completely cut when Ukraine diverted the Russian natural gas 
destined for Turkey. Veysel Atasoy, minister of energy and 
natural resources, went to Bulgaria to hold talks with a view to 
eliminating the shortage. The delegation headed by Atasoy will 
then to go to Ukraine to discuss the issue and tell Ukraine not 
to pump natural gas from the Turkey-Bulgaria-Romania pipeline. 
  According to information received from Ministry officials, 
after the natural gas supply was interrupted yesterday, 
reductions were made in the electricity, fertilizer, and 
manufacturing sectors. The reductions continue, but no 
reductions are planned for homes at this stage. 
  Of the natural gas consumed in Turkey, 11 percent is 
consumed 
in homes and 89 percent in the industrial sector. 

</TEXT>

