<H3> <TI>   Minister Returns After Bulgaria, Ukraine Gas Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1303073894 Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network in Turkish 
0530 GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1303073894 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara Turkiye Radyolari Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Veysel Atasoy, energy and natural resources 
minister, has stated that natural gas usage will be restored 
without any restrictions as of this evening. 
  Concluding his contacts in Bulgaria and Ukraine regarding 
natural gas usage, Atasoy returned to Turkey yesterday. Atasoy 
explained that the shortages in the natural gas delivery to 
Turkey have been eliminated after the two-day conflict between 
Russia and Ukraine was resolved following discussions regarding 
this issue. 
  Atasoy further stated that agreement was reached during his 
meeting with the chairman of the Bulgarian Committee on Power 
Supplies that Turkey will receive half of the natural gas 
delivered to Bulgaria. During his contacts in Kiev, Atasoy 
explained, he was assured of a continuous natural gas delivery 
as of 1600 today after the conflict between Russia and Ukraine 
were resolved. 

</TEXT>

