<H3> <TI>   Ciller Rules Out Negotiations With `Terrorists' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1303181194 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1600 
GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1303181194 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer-read report over still of Ciller] </F>
  [Text] Prime Minister Tansu Ciller has said that the 
government does not accept the terrorists as its equal adding 
that it is out of the question to ever sit at the negotiating 
table with these persons. 
  Ciller visited the children's hostel of the Child Protection 
Association in Istanbul's Kasimpasa quarter this afternoon. She 
exchanged holiday greetings and distributed gifts. In reply to 
a question, Ciller said: The terrorists cannot be our equals. 
We cannot consider them our equals. We, therefore, cannot sit 
at the negotiating table with them. The important issue is to 
ensure the security of life and property of our citizens in that 
region. We are able to celebrate the holidays in security 
throughout Turkey today. We will hold the elections in a 
similar atmosphere. Had these terrorists not existed we would 
have reached this point much earlier. The important issue now 
is for them to give up. The state is powerful. The Turkish 
state is very powerful. We are very determined. 

</TEXT>

