<H3> <TI>   Mentese on Results of Southeast Operations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA1303151794 Ankara TRT Television Network in Turkish 1100 
GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1303151794 </F>
<F P=104>  Ankara TRT Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Turkish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Announcer read report over still of Interior Minister Nahit </F>
Mentese] 
  [Text] Interior Minister Nahit Mentese has stated that 461 
terrorists have been killed and 2,189 captured during the 
security forces' operations since the beginning of the year, 
among them 365 who were killed and 1,271 who were captured in 
the state of emergency region. 
  Mentese noted that the terrorists and their supporters were 
in a panic as a result of not being able to resist the security 
forces as well as from suffering great losses. Mentese further 
stated that the terrorists are trying to solve their 
difficulties, which result from failure and the lack of support 
they receive from the people, by undertaking efforts to 
cooperate with foreigners. Mentese indicated that these 
developments are clear proof that certain foreign circles are 
using the terrorists as their tools. 
  Stating that it is unfortunate that there are parties and 
persons who boycott the regional elections in spite of the 
safety in the country established by the great sacrifices of the 
security forces, Mentese said that the political parties' duty 
of participating in the elections is a fundamental principle of 
democracy, adding that the people who avoid this duty will 
receive what they deserve from the people. 

</TEXT>

