<F P=100> FRANCE </F>
<H3> <TI>   Leotard Angered by Death of French Soldier in Bosnia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1103144494 Paris France-Inter Radio Network in French 1300 
GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1103144494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris France-Inter Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A French soldier was killed this morning in the 
Bihac area, in the western part of Bosnia. It is still not 
known who fired the shot. This is the 19th French soldier 
killed in former Yugoslavia. Francois Leotard heard the news 
while in Israel and the defense minister expressed his anger to 
Pierre Veil: 
  [Begin Leotard recording] As you can understand, my reaction 
is one of great sadness and anger. France is making sacrifices 
for peace. The soldiers who are targeted in this cowardly way 
are soldiers of peace. They are there to accomplish 
humanitarian missions. They escort food supplies and protect 
civilian populations. They are Blue Helmets, therefore they are 
not engaged in a war situation. War is often waged on them in a 
cowardly way. I express with great vigor my indignation at this 
kind of behavior. I hope that our mission there is understood 
despite all the difficulties encountered. Despite these 
victims, our mission is to bring peace to a war-torn region, 
which could pose a threat in the future. The French people 
should be aware of this. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

