<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Prime Minister Chernomyrdin Begins Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Meets With President Ahtisaari </H4>
<F P=102> LD1103122094 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1100 GMT 11 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1103122094 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Finnish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Martti Ahtisaari received firsthand 
information on the situation in Russia after his half-hour talks 
with Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin. Currently, a luncheon 
in honor of the Russian prime minister is beginning at the 
presidential palace. 
  Chernomyrdin started his two-day official visit to Finland 
in 
the morning. To begin with, there were bilateral talks between 
Chernomyrdin and Prime Minister Esko Aho. Prime Minister 
Chernomyrdin visited the Confederation of Finnish Industries and 
the Finnish Employers' Confederation in the morning. 
Representatives of Finnish industries raised the problems of 
financing in the trade between Finland and Russia. They hoped 
for concrete measures, especially in solving the problem of 
counterguarantees. An extensive business delegation is 
accompanying the Russian prime minister on his visit. 

</TEXT>

