<F P=100> AUSTRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Results of Provincial Diet Elections Reported </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  WA1303130894 Vienna ORF Teletext in German 2012 GMT 13 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> WA1303130894 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna ORF Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] Austrian state television reported the 
following results for the three provincial diet elections held 
on Sunday, 13 March 1994. In Carinthia, the Social Democratic 
Party of Austria (SPOe) led with 14 seats based on 37.4 percent 
of the vote, down 8.7 percent from the previous election. The 
Freedom Party of Austria (FPOe) won 13 seats with 33.4 percent 
of the vote, a gain of just under 5 percent. The Austrian 
People's Party (OeVP) obtained nine seats with 23.7 percent of 
the vote, a gain of 2.5 percent. The Greens and the Liberal 
Forum finished with 1.6 and 2.5 percent of the vote respectively 
but did not win any mandates. 
  In Salzburg, the OeVP captured 13 seats based on 38.6 
percent 
of the vote received, a decline of 5.4 percent from the previous 
election. The SPOe won 11 seats with 27.1 percent of the vote, 
down 4.1 percent. The FPOe finished with eight seats based on 
19.5 percent of the vote, up 3.1 percent. The Citizen's List 
won three seats with 7.2 percent of the vote, a gain of 1.1 
percent. The Liberal Forum received 5.7 percent of the vote, 
but has no seats in the diet. 
  The OeVP led again in Tyrol with 19 seats based on 47.3 
percent of the vote, a decline of 1.4 percent from the previous 
election. The SPOe finished with seven seats based on 19.9 
percent of the vote, a decline of 2.9 percent. The FPOe won 6 
seats with 16.2 percent of the vote, a gain of .6 percent. The 
Greens won four seats with 10.6 percent of the vote, a gain of 
2.3 percent. The Liberal Forum obtained 3.3 percent of the vote 
and did not win any seats. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

