<H3> <TI>   Change in Media Ownership Reviewed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1103124394 Vienna WIRTSCHAFTSWOCHE in German 10 Mar 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> AU1103124394 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna WIRTSCHAFTSWOCHE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Editorial by Christian S. Ortner] </F>
  [Text] Changes have been made in the group of 
WIRTSCHAFTSWOCHE shareholders. KURIER, which has so far held 
49.5 percent, is leaving and transferring its shares to the 
HANDELSBLATT publishing group, which now holds 99 percent of the 
company (1 percent still belongs to Peter Michael Lingens). 
Thus, the Austrian WIRTSCHAFTSWOCHE has finally been integrated 
in a highly reputed, international publishing group, which 
comprises publications such as HANDELSBLATT, the German 
WIRTSCHAFTSWOCHE, or the Swiss monthly BILANZ. In addition, 
linked with the group are the S. Fischer publishing house, the 
Rowohlt publishing house, the Droemersche publishing company, as 
well as SCIENTIFIC AMERICAN in the United States, to mention 
just a few. 
  These products and publishing companies have one thing in 
common -- a high standard which imposes a duty on us and gives 
you, the readers, the guarantee that WIRTSCHAFTSWOCHE's lead in 
quality will be steadily increased. 

</TEXT>

