<F P=103> AU1403134094 </F>
<F P=104>  Vienna ORF Teletext </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Following the defeat of the Social Democratic Party 
of Austria [SPOe] in the diet elections in Carinthia, the 
expected reshuffle was decided today: Health Minister Michael 
Ausserwinkler will replace the unfortunate SPOe Chairman Peter 
Ambrozy. Ambrozy will resign from all political functions. 
  Ausserwinkler immediately announced his claim to the 
position 
of provincial governor. It is logical that the representative 
of the party that got the most votes should become governor. 
The goal of the negotiations with the Austrian People's Party 
is a functioning government, he said. 

