<F P=101> Germany </F>
<H3> <TI>   Economics Ministry Predicts End of Recession </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU1503121794 Hamburg DPA in German 1044 GMT 15 Mar 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU1503121794 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> German </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Bonn (DPA) -- In the view of the Federal Economics 
Ministry, the west German economy will have overcome the 
recession by the end of March. In the first quarter of 1994, 
the real gross domestic product of the old laender will increase 
again over the same period of the previous year for the first 
time since the end of 1992, the ministry stated Tuesday [15 
March] in its monthly economic report. Despite the 0.5-percent 
decline from the third to the fourth quarter of 1993, economic 
activities have overcome the lowest point. 
  The last time the west German GDP achieved a real plus (0.9 
percent) compared to the same three-months period of the 
previous year was in the fourth quarter of 1992. In 1993, the 
decline in the first quarter was 3.4 percent but diminished in 
the course of the year to 1.9, 1.4, and finally 0.9 percent in 
the last quarter. 

</TEXT>

