<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   EU Commissioner on Cyprus, Confidence-Building Measures </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC1403195894 Nicosia CyBC Television Network in Greek 1830 
GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1403195894 </F>
<F P=104>  Nicosia CyBC Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Greek </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The European Union [EU] will evaluate the progress 
of efforts toward a solution of the Cyprus issue in January 1995 
based on the report of its observer [Serge Abou] and 
irrespective of whether or not the UN secretary general assigns 
blame to the interested parties. This was stated by EU Foreign 
Affairs Commissioner Hans Van Den Broek during the EU-Cyprus 
joint parliamentary committee meeting in Brussels. 
  [Begin recording] [unidentified correspondent] Speaking 
during the committee's meeting, EU Commissioner Van Den Broek 
said that the European Union supports the confidence-building 
measures and in the fourth financial protocol it is preparing 
for Cyprus, it is providing a special chapter on their 
implementation. Van Den Broek said that he will visit Cyprus on 
24 March. The Dutch commissioner said that it is uncertain if a 
solution could be found quickly. The EU Council of Ministers, 
he added, should evaluate the stance of the interested parties 
at the beginning of January 1995 and based on this evaluation 
should evaluate Cyprus' application for accession. The EU 
Council of Ministers' decision, he said, will be based on the EU 
observer's report irrespective of whether or not the UN 
secretary general assigns blame to the interested parties. 
  Foreign Minister Alekos Mikhailidhis stressed that it is 
very 
clear that the Turkish side is looking for ways to abandon the 
process or, at least through time-consuming discussions, make 
the process ineffective. 
  [Mikhailidhis] Despite all this, our side will continue full 
cooperation with the UN secretary general and his 
representatives. We are ready to discuss in a constructive way, 
with goodwill, and within the assigned timeframe in hope that 
such an agreement will be possible with the European Union's 
precious support. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

