<H3> <TI>   Ciampi: Need for European Political Structures </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403200894 Rome RAI Due Television Network in Italian 1845 
GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1403200894 </F>
<F P=104>  Rome RAI Due Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Italian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Carlo Azegio Ciampi, speaking at the 
Institute of International Affairs, touched upon the topics of 
the G-7 and the crisis in Europe. He said that Italy is working 
to ensure that Russia will participate more fully at the next 
meeting of G-7, which will be held in Naples. The prime 
minister added that the crisis in Yugoslavia is proof of a lack 
of a common European defense and security policy. Ciampi also 
warned that political integration must make progress in order to 
overcome recent setbacks. He said that without political 
structures, Europe is putting its future evolution at risk. 

</TEXT>

