<H3> <TI>   Peacekeeping Troops Leave for Croatia </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1503094294 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
0700 GMT 15 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1503094294 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Finnish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] More Finnish peacekeepers left Finland for the 
Balkans this morning. At the request of the UN, a troop of 39 
guards is being sent to Croatia. In this UN operation in 
Yugoslavia, Finland already has 230 men in The Former Yugoslav 
Republic of Macedonia. The Finnish guards will take up their 
duties tomorrow. The troops' task is to guard the service base 
and airfield at Pleso near Zagreb. 

