<F P=100> NORDIC COUNTRIES </F>
<F P=101> Finland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Food Industry Strike Hits Beer Supplies </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD1403120094 Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network in Finnish 
1100 GMT 14 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1403120094 </F>
<F P=104>  Helsinki Suomen Yleisradio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Finnish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The strike in the food industry has so far hit 
mainly beer lovers. Several retail stores ran out of beer last 
week and some restaurants, specializing in the sale of 
medium-strength beer, have already had to close their doors. In 
other respects, there have been sufficient quantities of food in 
the shops so far. This morning, all the basic necessities were 
still available almost as normal, but the situation may become 
somewhat more difficult in the next few days. The employers' 
organization in the food industry thinks that processed meat and 
fresh meat will disappear from the stores at the end of the week 
if the strike continues. 

</TEXT>

