<F P=106> [Report by Paul Verbraecken: "United Nations Requests </F>
Belgian Military for Tuzla Airport--Air Force To Man Control 
Towers of Disputed Airport"] 
  [Excerpt] On his way to Rwanda, Defense Minister Delcroix 
confirmed on Thursday [10 March] that the United Nations had 
formally requested Belgian military support for the reopening of 
Tuzla airport in Bosnia. The United Nations requests a 
contingent of 25 Belgian Air Force staff to man the control 
towers of this disputed airport. There is no mention of pilots. 

